djondb
========================================

djondb uses automake to generate the required files to compile on each
system, Linux, Mac, Windows, etc.

Prerequisites
========================================

autotools (automake, autoreconf, make)
libxss-dev
librt
libv8-dev (google javascript engine)
libX11-dev

Compilation
========================================

cd <DJONDB_DIR>/db
> autoreconf --install --force
> mkdir obj
> cd obj
> ../configure
> make
> sudo make install

If you want you can specify some flags at configure script, as follows:

--enable-debug      compiles with the debug symbols
--enable-log=X      Enables the log and specifies the level (0- low detail, 3 - maximum detail)
--enable-profile    Links djondb with profile information

Running
========================================


to start the server use the command:

> djondbd -n

this will start the server. If you want to shutdown just press Ctrl+C

to start the console use the command:

> djon-shell



Enjoy!


